Text: Look forward to working with Sec. of State Blinken, especially on the US strategy to counter China’s ambition of becoming the global superpower. Allowing China to surpass us economically, militarily & technologically would have detrimental consequences for America and the world.

Nearly 70% of Utah is owned by the federal government, putting our state at a disadvantage when it comes to decisions on management of our public lands. I will continue working at the federal level to ensure state & local leaders are brought to the table. https://t.co/I31CgQBWoK

National monuments have become a political football that gets tossed back and forth between administrations—like the recent executive order to review Utah’s Bears Ears and Grand Staircase-Escalante. The legislative process is the best way to end this political back and forth.

It's imperative that we continue to resist efforts to pack the Supreme Court and treat it as if it is one of the elected branches of government. Our society is only as strong as its institutions. We must ensure the integrity and independence of SCOTUS. https://t.co/jpAy6hXnPV

As @USTreasury Secretary, Dr. Yellen must be clear-eyed about the threats posed by the Chinese Communist Party—using economic tools at her disposal to counter the CCP’s malign activities & invest more in the sources of our domestic technological strength. https://t.co/C2rSSuVtsO

Members of the @UTNationalGuard and guard members around the country left their homes, jobs, and loved ones to travel to Washington in service of protecting our Capitol and our nation over the last several weeks. They deserve our greatest respect and our deepest gratitude. https://t.co/7VBelZ74dd

We urge the Biden administration to work with our state toward a collaborative, broadly supported solution regarding Grand Staircase-Escalante and Bears Ears National Monuments, instead of taking unilateral action. https://t.co/mmpAZRVA3y

I commend the Administration for following our calls to declare the CCP's mass internment, forced labor, and sterilization of Uyghurs as "genocide." The U.S. is the first country to do so, but it cannot be the last. The world must recognize these atrocities for what they are. https://t.co/KsbezuDtZq

The Senate should begin by passing our legislation to impose sanctions on Putin and the Russian officials complicit in the brazen poisoning of Alexei Navalny.
https://t.co/RmpcFPGKKn

The corruption and lawlessness of the Putin regime continues to be on full display for the world to see. The detention of Navalny is yet another shameless attempt by Putin to silence the Russian people’s fight for freedom and democracy. The U.S must hold him accountable. https://t.co/KNfIFRtcJq

Let us honor Dr. King’s legacy by looking inward. Let us learn to love and respect one another. It is on that foundation which we can engage with each other in a manner that celebrates our differences and mends the divisions among us.

To love our enemies is easier said than done, but it is necessary if we hope to heal our social sickness. When we demonstrate respect, understanding, and grace for each other, we become united. When we disparage or treat others with contempt, we deepen the rift that divides us.

Martin Luther King Jr. spoke often of the transformative nature of love. “Love is the only force capable of transforming an enemy into a friend.” Let this day be a renewed call for us to love people we disagree with, those who don’t share our opinions or viewpoints. #MLKDay

Thank you to @UTNationalGuard members deploying to DC today to offer support for the presidential inauguration. We deeply appreciate your dedication and commitment to protecting lives, property and ensuring a peaceful transition of power.

Given that this is being investigated by the Metropolitan Police Department's Homicide Branch, the United States Capitol Police and their federal partners, I hope the perpetrator who claimed Officer Sicknick's life is brought to justice.

Heartbroken by the death of Officer Brian Sicknick in the line of duty—protecting the Capitol and all of us inside. I join my colleagues and our entire Capitol Hill community in mourning this needless and tragic loss, and I pray for comfort for his loved ones and fellow officers.

Deep thanks to the frontline men & women of the @CapitolPolice, @FBI, @SecretService, other law enforcement & @NationalGuard who performed their missions today with an immense amount of professionalism & bravery. Grateful to you for keeping us safe every day, & especially today.

We must not be intimidated or prevented from fulfilling our constitutional duty. I urge my colleagues to move forward with completing the electoral count, to refrain from further objections, and to unanimously affirm the legitimacy of the presidential election.
The best way we can show respect for the voters who are upset is by telling them the truth. That is the burden, and the duty, of leadership.

Those who choose to continue to support his dangerous gambit by objecting to the results of a legitimate, democratic election will forever be seen as being complicit in an unprecedented attack against our democracy.
What happened at the U.S. Capitol today was an insurrection, incited by the President of the United States. https://t.co/NojKm86sZ2

Congratulations to @SpencerJCox and @DeidreHenderson on being sworn in as Utah’s Governor and Lt. Governor! Looking forward to working with you both in the coming years to advance Utah priorities here in Washington. https://t.co/qnQQuw8ZNO
Today marks 125 years of Utah statehood. Happy birthday to my beloved Utah! https://t.co/3GNBBOAwT1

Further attempts to cast doubt on the legitimacy of the 2020 Presidential election are contrary to the clearly expressed will of the American people. Congress must now fulfill its responsibility to certify the election results. It is time to move forward. https://t.co/tDhA5PvccM
The egregious ploy to reject electors may enhance the political ambition of some, but dangerously threatens our Democratic Republic. https://t.co/jKEvoXskbl

The vaccination program is falling woefully behind. With hundreds of thousands of lives at stake, urgent action is needed on a comprehensive vaccination plan that states can use as a model. https://t.co/M6gvUyUKmv

A dedicated teacher and legislator, Rep. Lou Shurtliff worked tirelessly in service to others. Her passing is a sad loss for Utah. Ann and I send our prayers to her loved ones during this difficult time. https://t.co/iwS0usL5BI

.@GovHerbert has led our state so well over these past 11.5 years. His dedication to the service of Utahns has been admirable. Ann and I wish you and Jeanette well as you embark on this next chapter! https://t.co/ZJFcT4ecCy

Proud to see this bill bringing clean water to Utah Navajos signed into law after a years-long, hard fought effort. The lack of running water has only exacerbated Navajo Nation’s struggle with #COVID19. https://t.co/1ujMi6q4C2

Relieved that this long-awaited, bipartisan emergency #COVID19 legislation has finally been signed into law. Help is now on the way to workers, families, and small businesses across the country who are desperately in need.

Americans are in urgent need for emergency #COVID19 relief—lifelines like food, shelter, unemployment benefits, and small business relief. The President must immediately sign or veto the COVID-19 relief package so Congress can act before it's too late. https://t.co/54XdZRCmju

Navajo Nation has some of the highest #COVID19 infection rates in the country—largely impacted by the lack of running in nearly half of homes. After a years-long, hard fought effort, the government funding bill passed last night will bring clean water to Utah Navajos. https://t.co/6WAKPVIU60

My statement on the government funding bill, which provides emergency #COVID19 relief, secures clean water for Utah’s Navajos, ends surprise medical billing, supports @HAFB, and helps Utah’s rural communities: https://t.co/mXUvMbaFD3

The emergency relief package passed by Congress provides a critical lifeline to Americans who are struggling as a result of the pandemic. Help is on the way for thousands of unemployed workers, small business owners, and families who have been hardest hit. https://t.co/1XhwLgrMbS

Proud that our bipartisan legislation became the foundation of the final #COVID19 relief package, which includes our provisions to extend federal unemployment benefits, provide relief for small businesses, and authorize funding to support health providers & vaccine distribution.

Congress has finally agreed on a #COVID19 emergency relief package using our consensus bill as the foundation. Workers, businesses, and families need help now. We urge our colleagues to quickly pass this bill, and for the President to sign it into law. https://t.co/Aa3CpPW89d

Our most urgent task is to get emergency #COVID19 relief across the finish line. I look to Congressional leadership to finalize the bill, hopefully in a way that is consistent with much of the bipartisan proposal we presented earlier this week. https://t.co/Wh58zr83IN

For continuity of government purposes, the attending physician has informed us that senators are to receive vaccination, and that there’s no reason to delay. Accordingly, I will receive the vaccine. I will also continue to wear a mask, social distance and avoid large gatherings.
https://t.co/iEsWD1V4KI

Utahns—for information regarding our state’s #COVID19 vaccine distribution plan, check out: https://t.co/BeXdhn8YgL. Distribution of these vaccines is great news—especially for our front line health workers. We must work to increase Americans' confidence in these vaccines. https://t.co/YWDs59JwoH

We urge Senate and House leadership and the White House to take up our bipartisan legislation now. Congress should not leave town before passing an emergency #COVID19 relief package. https://t.co/u1nWmY1XK8

Our bipartisan #COVID19 legislation provides the emergency relief our nation desperately needs:
✔️small business relief
✔️unemployment insurance extension
✔️funding for vaccines & health care providers
✔️state & local assistance
✔️national liability shield
https://t.co/NmM6UYeZVD

The #COVID19 crisis is taking a toll on our country—people are really hurting. During a crisis, it is essential that we come together to do what is necessary. That’s what our bipartisan, bicameral emergency COVID-19 relief legislation does. Learn more: https://t.co/vm46pLft3n

This delivery of #COVID19 vaccines is great news for Utah, especially the front line workers who have worked tirelessly to care for our communities. The federal government must work diligently to increase the confidence individuals have in these vaccines. https://t.co/kedzKokq0K

Our bipartisan group reached agreement on a two part #COVID19 relief package that includes relief for small businesses, unemployment insurance, funding for vaccines & health care providers, state & local assistance, and a national liability shield for COVID-related lawsuits. https://t.co/ZYHEWgiSeD
Bipartisan Group of Senators Announce COVID-19 Relief Legislation https://t.co/TN5RBwlQwa

The #FY21NDAA includes provisions which will push back against Chinese and Russian aggression, limit the reduction of US troops from Germany, and continue to support the critical work of Utah’s @HAFB. Pleased the NDAA overwhelmingly passed the Senate. https://t.co/08gQCaQHkH

Utah’s federal courthouse will soon be named in honor of Senator Orrin Hatch, who is one of our country’s most dedicated public servants. Pleased to see this bill headed to the President’s desk and I look forward to seeing Senator Hatch’s name on our courthouse building. https://t.co/NpkzAMz46A
The attack on Pearl Harbor occurred 79 years ago today. Let us honor those brave Americans who lost their lives that day and vow to never forget their service and sacrifice 🇺🇸 https://t.co/xCk4wtFIZ8

Congress made the right decision by including a provision in the NDAA to prevent a significant withdrawal of American troops from Germany. We should be focused on linking arms with our allies to address threats from Russia and China—not offending them. https://t.co/TFTtdm9mRF

Yesterday, I joined a group of colleagues to announce a bipartisan, bicameral #COVID19 emergency relief framework that will help American students, families, businesses, workers, and health care providers during this crisis. Learn more about our framework: https://t.co/Yx5BTaf0kb

Our bipartisan, bicameral #COVID19 emergency relief framework is not a $1.8 trillion stimulus bill—it's a relief measure half that amount. Americans are in urgent need of additional COVID-19 relief and Congress must deliver. I urge my colleagues to come together on a deal. https://t.co/RHtFnkpUNk

Americans are in urgent need of #COVID19 relief. I’m teaming up with a bipartisan group of colleagues to announce a COVID-19 emergency relief framework that will help American families, businesses, workers, and health care providers during this crisis. https://t.co/xAaKWl4iX6
